(* Theorem: 1 < p /\ 0 < n ==> (p ** (n DIV 2) - 2) * p ** (n DIV 2) <= p ** n - 2 * p ** (n DIV 2) *)
(* Proof:
   Let m = n DIV 2, q = p ** m.
   The goal becomes: (q - 2) * q <= p ** n - 2 * q
   If n = 1,
      Then m = 0                    by ONE_DIV, 0 < 2.
       and q = 1                    by EXP
